<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871106-0071 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Resdel Industries</HL><DD> 11/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> RSDL RELTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK) </IN><TEXT>   RESDEL INDUSTRIES said it completed the previously announced sale of $10 million of a newly created issue of 9 1/2% cumulative convertible exchangeable preferred stock to a unit of Reliance Financial Services Corp. for $5.5 million and Reliance's 6.9% stake in Resdel's common stock. Resdel is an Arcadia, Calif.-based supplier of electronic subsystems and parts for U.S. government avionics, security, electronic warfare and anti-submarine warfare systems. The company said it will retire the 443,100 of its shares that were held by Reliance, a New York concern controlled by investor Saul P. Steinberg. The new preferred is exchangeable under certain circumstances into 10 1/2% convertible subordinated notes due October 1992, and both the preferred stock and notes are convertible into shares of Resdel at $5.50 a share. In a related matter, Resdel said its employee stock ownership plan bought 200,000 shares of Resdel stock. </TEXT></DOC>